==Normative Ethics==

{{main|Normative Ethics}}
 
Traditionally, normative ethics (also known as moral theory) was the study what makes actions right and wrong. Classical theories in this vein include [[utilitarianism]], [[Kantianism]], and some forms of [[contractarianism]]. These theories offered an overarching moral principle to which one could appeal in resolving difficult moral decisions.
